# InSync Internal Constitution

## Project Overview
**Project Name:** InSync

## Design & Branding Guidelines

### Color Palette
- **Thomson Reuters Orange:** #FA6400
- **White:** #FFFFFF  
- **Dark Gray:** #404040

*Note: Always use these official Thomson Reuters colors for consistency across the application.*

### Logo Integration
- Use the official Thomson Reuters logo from: https://share.google/YXTobWekgPC5m7RBk
- Align Thomson Reuters logo with custom-designed InSync logo in the header
- Maintain proper branding hierarchy and visual balance

## Business Logic Requirements

### Seat Map Configuration
- **Fixed Grid:** Office contains 34 seats with naming convention: 1820-10F-067 through 1820-10F-100
- **Extensibility:** Managers must have administrative capability to add additional seat names as needed
- **Management Access:** Provide interface for seat configuration management

### RTO (Return to Office) Calculation
- **Target Percentage:** 40%
- **Formula:** Required Days = (Total Mon-Fri) - (Holidays + Site-WFH + User Leaves + WFA) * 0.4
- **Rounding:** Always round up the final result
- **Calculation Notes:** 
  - Total Mon-Fri = Total weekdays in calculation period
  - Holidays = Company holidays
  - Site-WFH = Site-designated work from home days
  - User Leaves = Individual employee leave days
  - WFA = Work from anywhere days

## Security & Access Control

### Email Domain Restriction
- **Requirement:** Restrict ALL access and registration to @thomsonreuters.com email addresses ONLY
- **Implementation:** Validate email domain during registration and authentication
- **No Exceptions:** External email domains must be blocked

## Technical Stack Requirements

### Core Technologies
- **Frontend Framework:** TypeScript
- **Styling:** Tailwind CSS
- **Build Tool:** Vite
- **Database:** Supabase

### Environment Variables
- **Supabase Configuration:** ALWAYS use environment variables for Supabase keys
- **Security:** Never hardcode API keys or sensitive configuration in source code
- **Required Variables:**
  - VITE_SUPABASE_URL
  - VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
  - (Additional Supabase environment variables as needed)

## Development Standards

### Code Quality
- Use TypeScript strict mode
- Implement proper error handling
- Follow consistent naming conventions
- Maintain clean, readable code structure

### UI/UX Standards
- Maintain Thomson Reuters brand consistency
- Ensure responsive design across devices
- Implement accessible design principles
- Use consistent spacing and typography

---

*This constitution serves as the foundational guidelines for the InSync project development. All team members and contributors must adhere to these specifications.*